This example adds 2 DPU instances and 1 Multiscaler instance to the 'zcu104_vcu' platform.

##############
Building steps
##############

1. Source 2021.1 Vitis build and petalinux build

2. Build 'zcu104_vcu' platform 
    git clone https://gitenterprise.xilinx.com/IPS-SSW/ivas-platforms.git
    cd Embedded/zcu104_vcu
    make

3. Download the DPU TRD 
    git clone https://gitenterprise.xilinx.com/aisw/DPU_TRD.git

4. Download the multiscaler kernel 
    git clone https://gitenterprise.xilinx.com/IPS-SSW/ivas-accel-hw.git

5. Compile the example design
    make PLATFORM=<Path_to_xpfm_file> DPU_TRD_PATH=<Path_to_DPU_TRD> HW_ACCEL_PATH=<Path_to_multiscaler>

6. Once build is completed, the SD card image, binary_container_1/sd_card.img, can be flashed on SD card using balenaEtcher tool

#####################################
Example Application Compilation Steps
#####################################

1. Setup the cross compilation environment.

   1.1 Install the sysroot SDK (sdk.sh) from petalinux build.
       cd <path to>/vas-platforms/Embedded/zcu104_vcu/petalinux/images/linux/
       ./sdk.sh -y -d <Folder path to install SDK>

   1.2 Source the environment generated in SDK installation folder.
       source <Folder path where SDK is installed>/environment-setup-cortexa72-cortexa53-xilinx-linux

2. Compile the example application.
   cd <Path to>/ivas-examples/Embedded/smart_model_select/src 
   make SYSROOT=<Folder path where SDK is installed>/sysroots/cortexa72-cortexa53-xilinx-linux/
